{"word":"H2224 - זָרַח - zârach - zaw-rakh' - Arise","slug":"H2224","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">זָרַח</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>zârach"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>zaw-rakh'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Arise"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D6;&#x05E8;&#x05D7; - za&#x0302;rach</b> - <i>zaw-rakh'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>irradiate</i> (or shoot forth beams), that is, to <i>rise</i> (as the sun); specifically to <i>appear</i> (as a symptom of leprosy): - arise, rise (up), as soon as it is up."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H2225\">H2225</a>, <a href=\"#/H2226\">H2226</a>, <a href=\"#/H2227\">H2227</a>, <a href=\"#/H2228\">H2228</a>, <a href=\"#/H249\">H249</a>, <a href=\"#/H250\">H250</a>, <a href=\"#/H3155\">H3155</a>, <a href=\"#/H3156\">H3156</a>, <a href=\"#/H4217\">H4217</a>"}]}